{"name":"Vevnu, Lady of Time","size":"gargantuan","type":"dragon","tag":"time dragon","alignment":"lawful neutral","hitDice":"5","armorName":"natural armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":10,"otherArmorDesc":"10","speed":"40","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"40","flySpeed":"80","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"536 (29d20 + 232)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"28","dexPoints":"14","conPoints":"26","intPoints":"27","wisPoints":"18","chaPoints":"23","blindsight":"60","blind":false,"darkvision":"120","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"26","customCr":"1 (200 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":true,"legendariesDescription":"","isLair":true,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, Vevnu can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), she can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"Vevnu can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the monster's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":true,"regionalDescription":"The region surrounding an Vevnu's lair is altered by the her magic, creating one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the Vevnu dies, the effects fade over the course of 1d100 years, but only if the steely egg that contains Vevnu's next body is removed from her lair.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Cycle of Rebirth","desc":"If Vevnu dies, her soul coalesces into a steely egg and teleports to a random plane of existence. The egg is immune to all damage and hatches into a time dragon wyrmling after 1d100 years. The dragon retains all memories and knowledge it gained in its previous life."},{"name":"Legendary Resistance (5/day)","desc":"If Vevnu fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead."},{"name":"Innate Spellcasting","desc":"Vevnu's spellcasting ability is Intelligence (spell save DC [INT SAVE], [INT ATK] to hit with spell attacks). It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:\n\n> At will: _Deja Vu, Expeditious Retreat, Fast-Forward/Reverse, Grist, Halt, Haste, Hurry/Delay, Purge, Slow, Time Capsule, Time's Arrow, Undo-Harm_\n> 3/day each: _Alavar's Spacetime Anomaly, Curse of Aging, Curse of Youth, Ephemeral Ward, Erase, Move Heavens, Novice, Prescience, Vevnu's Cycle of Misplacement_\n> 1/day each: _Rewind, Sequester, Temporal Bubble, Time Stop, Time Travel_"}],"actions":[{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"Vevnu makes three Rend attacks."},{"name":"Rend","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 15 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 3D8] slashing damage plus [3d6] force damage."},{"name":"Time Breath (Recharge 5-6)","desc":"Vevnu exhales a wave of shimmering light in a 90-foot cone. Nonmagical objects and vegetation in that area that aren't being worn or carried crumble to dust. Each creature in that area must make a DC [CON SAVE] Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes [8d12] force damage and is magically weakened as it is desynchronized from the time stream. While the creature is in this state, attack rolls against it have advantage, it has the poisoned condition, and other creatures have resistance to all damage it deals. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage only. A weakened creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself after it succeeds on three of these saves."},{"name":"Time Gate (1/Day)","desc":"Vevnu conjures a 20-foot-diameter, circular portal in the space between her horns or in an unoccupied space it can see within 30 feet of itself. The portal links to a precise location on any plane of existence at a point in time up to 8,000 years from the present, whether past of future. The portal lasts for 24 hours or until the dragon's concentration ends (as if concentrating on a spell). The portal has a front and a back on each plane where it appears. Travel through the portal is possible only by moving through its front. Anything that does so is transported to the destination, appearing in the unoccupied space nearest to the portal. Deities and other planar rulers can prevent portals created by the dragon from opening in the rulers' presence or anywhere within their domains."}],"bonusActions":[],"reactions":[{"name":"Multireaction","desc":"Vevnu can take up to three reactions per round but only one per turn."},{"name":"Reactive Rend","desc":"After using Legendary Resistance or in response to being hit by an attack roll, the dragon makes one Rend attack."},{"name":"Slow Time","desc":"Immediately after a creature Vevnu can see ends its turn, she targets a she can see within 90 feet of herself that is weakened by her Time Breath. Until the weakened effect ends on the target, its speed becomes 0, and its speed can't increase."},{"name":"Time Slip","desc":"Vevnu halves the damage she takes from an attack made against her, provided she can see the attacker. The dragon can then immediately teleport, along with any equipment she's wearing or carrying, up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space she can see."}],"legendaries":[],"mythics":[],"lairs":[{"name":"Temporal Fling","desc":"Vevnu attempts to fling a creature it can see within 60 feet of herself forward through time. The target must succeed a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw or take [4d12] psychic damage and move 1 round forward in time. A target moved forward in time vanishes for the duration. When the effect ends, the target reappears in the space it left or in an unoccupied space nearest to that space if it's occupied."},{"name":"Temporal Lag","desc":"Vevnu slows time for each creature within 60 feet of herself. Until initiative count 20 of the next round, the affected creature can move or take an action on its turn, not both. The creature also can't take a reaction or a bonus action."},{"name":"Timeline Divergence","desc":"Vevnu chooses a space it can fit into within its lair. She exists simultaneously in her space and the chosen space until initiative count 20 on the next round. Whenever she moves or takes an action, she chooses which version is moving or acting. If an effect or attack can target both of her spaces at the same time, she is affected only once."}],"regionals":[{"name":"Time Dilations","desc":"Time fluctuates within 3 miles of the lair. Short rests taken within this area take 10 minutes or 2 hours (Random / Vevnu's choice)."},{"name":"Timelessness","desc":"Beasts, Humanoids, and Plants within 3 miles of the lair age only 1 year for every 10 years that pass."},{"name":"A Space Between Time","desc":"The area within 3 miles of the lair exists sinusoidal to the normal flow of time. The space where the lair is does not always take up its physical location and exists at different periods of time. Therefore, follow these rules:\n\nOnce per month, roll a 3d30. Those days are the days during that month the lair will occupy it's physical space.\n\nWhen leaving the lair, a creature must roll a 1d100. \n- 1: 1d1000 years forward in time. \n- 2: 1d1000 years back in time. \n- 3-12: 1d100 years forward in time. \n- 13-20: 1d100 years back in time. \n- 21-30: 1d10 years forward in time. \n- 31-40: 1d10 years back in time.\n- 41-50: 1d100 days forward in time.\n- 51-60: 1d100 days back in time.\n- 61-70: 1d10 days forward in time.\n- 71-80: 1d10 days back in time.\n- 81-90: Same day that creature entered the lair.\n- 91-99: Creature's desired time destination.\n- 100: Creature's desired time and space destination."}],"sthrows":[],"skills":[{"name":"arcana","stat":"int"},{"name":"history","stat":"int","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"perception","stat":"wis","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"stealth","stat":"dex","note":" (ex)"}],"damagetypes":[],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[],"languages":[{"name":"All","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":7,"damage":[]}